wikipedia_page.main: Derek Edmund Teden (19 July 1916 – 15 October 1940(1940-10-15) (aged 24)) was an English rugby union player.  He won three caps in the 1939 Home Nations Championship.  During the Second World War he served as Pilot Officer with the RAF Coastal Command, and disappeared in 1940 on an anti-invasion patrol with No. 206 Squadron RAF.  He is commemorated on the Runnymede Memorial.
